fields.name: Steve
fields.description_short: Three men search for Steve, wonder who He is, think about God, die.
fields.description_long: The triplet of Benjamin Beckmann, Marcel Williams, and Oscar Silvio take on our latest play; Steve by Stephen Belber.

fields.name: The Winter’s Tale
fields.description_short: Shakespeare's gap in his geographical knowledge makes no difference to the quality of this romantic tragedy.
fields.description_long: The jealous King Leontes falsely accuses his wife, Hermione of infidelity with his best friend, and she dies. Leontes exiles his newborn daughter Perdita, who is raised by shepherds for sixteen years and falls in love with the son of Leontes' friend. When Perdita returns home, a statue of Hermione "comes to life", and everyone is reconciled.

fields.name: Asako Hada & The Lumberjacks
fields.description_short: A unique musical comedy about work life.
fields.description_long: Asako and her team of weird and whacky musicians and their equally weird and whacky instruments take us on a musical journey.

fields.name: The Pilgrim's Respite
fields.description: A cosy interior for intimate performances. The Pilgrims Respite is our smallest theatre and is usually used for plays, comedy acts and lectures.

fields.name: Maestro's Muse
fields.description: This is our largest concert hall, used for orchestral performances and theatrical performances.
